628
00:53:04,560 --> 00:53:04,860
 Right.

629
00:53:05,520 --> 00:53:15,000
 Um, and so it turned out Jerry is the name of the leader and, uh, and he began to talk with me and we just, you know, exchange phone numbers.

630
00:53:15,000 --> 00:53:23,700
 And, uh, he, you know, asked me if he could share this with all the other volunteers so that everybody could pray for me specifically for me.

631
00:53:23,700 --> 00:53:28,300
 And, um, I said, of course, you know, I, I need all the prayers.

632
00:53:28,300 --> 00:53:31,080
 I need, I need all the prayers, you know, I need to find another job.

633
00:53:31,540 --> 00:53:52,660
 And, and it was interesting because during that time of the campaign, I, there was such a, a dramatic shift in, um, in my personal life, in the way that I viewed, um, not just my own relationship with God, but also the way I viewed Christians as a whole.

634
00:53:52,660 --> 00:54:00,800
 It was really the first time that I saw the body of Christ embodied physically in, in others.

635
00:54:01,140 --> 00:54:18,980
 Oftentimes, I think I would look at Christians as being hypocrites and I never really saw them truly, um, behave in a way that was genuine and nonjudgmental.

636
00:54:19,360 --> 00:54:29,960
 And, and, and that was really the first time that I saw Christ physically embodied in these people who were so merciful to me, who were so loving.

637
00:54:29,960 --> 00:54:31,680
 And it was beautiful.

638
00:54:31,680 --> 00:54:41,540
 It was beautiful because they were so supportive and they were, you know, encouraging me to leave my job and, and saying, you know, we will support you, we'll help you.

639
00:54:41,580 --> 00:54:48,860
 And I said, I had such a hard time believing that, you know, I, I, I didn't know how to trust God.

640
00:54:49,900 --> 00:54:58,120
 And if I didn't know how to trust God, how was I going to trust these strangers who were saying, you know, we will help you, Ramona, we're going to help you.

641
00:54:58,120 --> 00:55:05,140
 And I thought, no, you know, I don't, I don't, I don't know if I can believe that or, or you're just, or maybe I'm just going to be abandoned, you know.

642
00:55:05,140 --> 00:55:12,220
 And I had all of these broken relationships in my life, but the biggest broken relationship I had was with Jesus.

643
00:55:12,220 --> 00:55:20,980
 And I think, you know, when we don't have that relationship with God and with Christ, it's so difficult to navigate our lives.

644
00:55:21,460 --> 00:55:37,800
 And that was, that was really the test for me was how do I regain my relationship with Christ so that I could trust God and then in turn trust the body of Christ, you know, that is physically here to help us and help me.

645
00:55:39,140 --> 00:55:50,740
 And so that was part of that journey during that 40 days was regaining my trust in the Lord and then also seeing him embodied in the people who were loving me.

646
00:55:50,740 --> 00:55:55,100
 And I always tell people I was loved out of the abortion industry.

647
00:55:55,100 --> 00:56:00,960
 I was prayed out of the abortion industry, but I was also loved out of the abortion industry.

648
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:06,080
 And at the end of the 40 days, I was still at Planned Parenthood.

649
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:13,420
 I thought, surely, you know, I would find the new job and I would move on and, you know, and no, you know, God had other plans.

650
00:56:13,420 --> 00:56:17,220
 And so at the end of 40 days, I was still there.

651
00:56:17,220 --> 00:56:21,780
 And I remember going to Easter Mass with my family.

652
00:56:21,780 --> 00:56:25,060
 At that point, you know, we were going back to Mass every Sunday.

653
00:56:25,060 --> 00:56:27,520
 I had stopped using contraception.

654
00:56:27,520 --> 00:56:34,180
 I had embraced natural family planning, which was another part of the miracle because many couples,

655
00:56:34,340 --> 00:56:41,180
 and many married couples really struggle with, you know, utilizing natural family planning instead of contraception.

656
00:56:41,180 --> 00:56:48,380
 And I realize now it was such a miracle because I told my husband, I'm not going to use birth control anymore.

657
00:56:48,380 --> 00:56:50,640
 I was just like, I'm not going to do it.

658
00:56:51,060 --> 00:56:59,440
 And there's a method that I can learn to where we can naturally, you know, track our fertility.

659
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,700
 And my husband said, okay.

660
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:05,320
 And I said, you know, it was easy.

661
00:57:05,320 --> 00:57:13,760
 And I didn't realize it until now, you know, later on that, wow, that was actually a miracle because it's normally not easy for couples to do that.

662
00:57:13,840 --> 00:57:17,160
 You know, either the wife is okay and the husband isn't or vice versa.

663
00:57:17,160 --> 00:57:26,220
 And, and so that was part of the journey as well was in, you know, utilizing natural family planning and not using contraception.

664
00:57:26,720 --> 00:57:37,280
 And so, you know, there was just, just an incredible time, but we were going back, you know, we were attending mass every Sunday and we'd gone to Easter Sunday mass.

665
00:57:37,440 --> 00:57:42,100
 And I went back to work, you know, on the following Tuesday on Easter Tuesday.

666
00:57:42,100 --> 00:57:47,000
 And it was the first time that I was very depressed.

667
00:57:47,000 --> 00:57:51,260
 During those 40 days, I was happy and full of joy.

668
00:57:51,260 --> 00:57:56,360
 And I had so much hope, you know, there was just so much hope for the future.

669
00:57:56,360 --> 00:58:01,100
 And, you know, I had all of these people, you know, praying for me and supporting me.

670
00:58:01,100 --> 00:58:05,080
 And, and that was the first time that I was really, really depressed.

671
00:58:05,400 --> 00:58:13,480
 And I left work that evening really down and almost in despair.

672
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:18,660
 The 40 days campaign, it ended, you know, no one was on the sidewalk anymore.

673
00:58:18,660 --> 00:58:26,300
 I was still in touch and in contact with those from 40 days for life and with Jerry, but I just felt very alone.

674
00:58:26,740 --> 00:58:34,220
 And I remember I had a, a 25 minute drive home and it was the first time that I'd driven in silence.

675
00:58:34,220 --> 00:58:38,500
 No radio, no music, nothing, just me and God.

676
00:58:39,440 --> 00:58:51,640
 And I was crying out to the Lord and just really angry with him and asking him why, why I was, why, you know, God, why am I going through all of this, you know?

677
00:58:52,160 --> 00:58:59,060
 But really questioning, you know, how he expected me to leave my job if I didn't have another job, you know?

678
00:58:59,060 --> 00:59:02,960
 And we needed, we needed that extra income to survive.

679
00:59:03,540 --> 00:59:07,400
 And, and, and I was like, God, you know, I've done everything you've asked me to do.

680
00:59:07,400 --> 00:59:15,040
 You know, I'm not contraceptive, I'm praying the rosary, I'm going back to church, you know, I'm, I'm doing everything that you asked.

681
00:59:15,040 --> 00:59:20,120
 I understand that I shouldn't work here anymore, but give me an out.

682
00:59:20,540 --> 00:59:26,000
 You're not giving me a way out and I don't know why you have left me abandoned.

683
00:59:26,000 --> 00:59:34,760
 And then I pulled into my driveway at my home and I sat there in my car just for a little bit in silence.

684
00:59:34,760 --> 00:59:40,720
 And that's when I turned on the radio and everything changed at that point.

685
00:59:40,720 --> 00:59:48,360
 There was a radio program on that, I guess it had just started and it was already preset to Catholic radio.

686
00:59:48,360 --> 01:00:00,460
 So when I turned it on at that moment, this, this gentleman called in and he was talking about all the years that he had spent praying in front of his local abortion facility,

687
01:00:00,460 --> 01:00:04,260
 which had been like 35 years or something crazy, extraordinary.

688
01:00:04,260 --> 01:00:14,480
 And he spoke of, you know, how important it was for him to defend life, to be there, to pray, to try to, you know, get women to choose life.

689
01:00:14,920 --> 01:00:20,500
 And the radio host said to him, the words that just completely transformed me.

690
01:00:20,500 --> 01:00:24,300
 And she said, thank you for all that you do for the unborn.

691
01:00:24,300 --> 01:00:29,980
 Thank you for your witness, for your defense of, of the defenseless.

692
01:00:29,980 --> 01:00:34,180
 And, and she said, at the end of our lives, we're all going to stand before God.

693
01:00:34,180 --> 01:00:39,280
 And we're all, and God is going to ask you, did you know about abortion?

694
01:00:39,920 --> 01:00:47,240
 And then he's going to ask you, did you know that babies were being ripped from their mother's wombs, limb by limb at the rate of 3000 a day?

695
01:00:47,240 --> 01:00:50,080
 And then he's going to ask you, what did you do?

696
01:00:51,020 --> 01:00:53,740
 And when she finished those words, what did you do?

697
01:00:53,740 --> 01:00:58,360
 I began to weep and just weep uncontrollably.

698
01:00:58,360 --> 01:01:14,020
 I think at that moment, there was such a, I was just so grief, grief stricken, because I realized I saw myself as a child, as a little girl standing before God at the end of my life.

699
01:01:14,100 --> 01:01:21,980
 But for some reason, I was seeing myself as a child, which I think, you know, is significant.

700
01:01:21,980 --> 01:01:28,340
 But, but I was seeing myself as a child standing before God and him saying, Ramona, did you know?

701
01:01:28,340 --> 01:01:30,020
 And what did you do?

702
01:01:30,020 --> 01:01:38,860
 And I think at those words, what did you do is when I realized that I had for three years, been complicit in the deaths of innocent babies.

703
01:01:40,340 --> 01:01:47,320
 For three years, I tried to defend my position that, oh, I'm just referring women for abortion.

704
01:01:47,320 --> 01:01:50,900
 It's their choice, whether they do it, whether they don't do it.

705
01:01:50,900 --> 01:01:52,100
 That's not on me.

706
01:01:52,100 --> 01:01:54,880
 I'm not responsible for what they choose.

707
01:01:55,640 --> 01:02:07,500
 And it was in that moment that I realized that I was responsible, because at the end of the day, it didn't, it, while it mattered what a woman chose, yes, she has the free will to choose.

708
01:02:07,500 --> 01:02:18,920
 But I also was responsible for not defending life, even if that resulted in the abortion of those babies, that I still had to defend life.

709
01:02:20,120 --> 01:02:32,020
 And I think that was that fight, that moment where I realized that this euphemism of choice, a woman's right to choose, is simply just a euphemism.

710
01:02:32,020 --> 01:02:43,400
 You know, it is, it is words to get us to be distracted from the reality of what is abortion, because we don't want to say abortion, a woman's right to choose abortion.

711
01:02:43,400 --> 01:02:47,860
 We just call it choice, or we call it reproductive health care, right?

712
01:02:47,860 --> 01:02:52,780
 Or just, you know, health care in general, right?

713
01:02:52,780 --> 01:03:04,420
 We use all of these euphemisms to try to make abortion more palatable for us to be more accepting of what it is, because we want to ignore what abortion really is.

714
01:03:05,020 --> 01:03:18,440
 And I think I really had spent all of my life buying into the lie of choice, and being deceived by those words, pro-choice, and a woman's right to choose.

715
01:03:18,440 --> 01:03:22,060
 I had spent all of my life being deceived by those words.

716
01:03:22,480 --> 01:03:32,840
 And it was in that moment I realized, yeah, I have blood on my hands, because I was helping women obtain abortions.

717
01:03:32,840 --> 01:03:36,720
 I was very complicit in that.

718
01:03:37,100 --> 01:03:49,480
 And when you, when you come to that moment in your life where you realize what you've been involved in, and in this case, the death of human beings, the innocent, the most innocent among us, right?

719
01:03:49,480 --> 01:03:57,240
 It is very hard, very, very difficult, very painful to accept that reality.

720
01:03:57,240 --> 01:04:03,140
 And yet, at the same time, it was also such a beautiful moment of God's mercy.

721
01:04:03,920 --> 01:04:15,180
 And as much as it hurt me, as much as I was broken, heartbroken, there was also this beautiful moment where I felt God's love very, very deeply in that moment.

722
01:04:15,180 --> 01:04:17,580
 So it wasn't like I was being scolded.

723
01:04:17,580 --> 01:04:20,920
 It was that God was saying, I love you.

724
01:04:20,920 --> 01:04:25,080
 And I love you so much that you have to see what you've done.

725
01:04:25,080 --> 01:04:27,640
 And it was beautiful.

726
01:04:27,640 --> 01:04:28,820
 It was a beautiful moment.

727
01:04:28,820 --> 01:04:37,900
 And I do, I knew right then, that, that would apply to everything in my life.

728
01:04:37,900 --> 01:04:40,300
 What did you do?

729
01:04:40,300 --> 01:04:43,400
 You know, what did you do when your neighbor was thirsty?

730
01:04:43,400 --> 01:04:45,720
 What did you do when your neighbor was hungry?

731
01:04:45,720 --> 01:04:48,840
 You know, what did you do when someone needed clothing?

732
01:04:49,120 --> 01:04:54,900
 You know, all of those things that we turn away from, you know, that we didn't do the right thing.

733
01:04:54,900 --> 01:04:59,360
 That I would always be held accountable for what I did and what I didn't do.

734
01:05:00,380 --> 01:05:09,560
 And I think, you know, just moving forward from that, I realized that my life would never be the same from that moment on.

735
01:05:09,560 --> 01:05:17,820
 And so I dried off my tears and I went in the house and I just began to cry again.

736
01:05:18,260 --> 01:05:22,880
 And my husband, God bless him, he was frightened because he thought, what is going on, you know?

737
01:05:22,880 --> 01:05:26,140
 And I just fell into his arms and I began to cry.

738
01:05:26,140 --> 01:05:27,380
 And I said, I'm going to go to hell.

739
01:05:27,380 --> 01:05:28,980
 And he said, no, you're not.

740
01:05:28,980 --> 01:05:30,640
 No, you're not.

741
01:05:30,640 --> 01:05:32,180
 And he comforted me.

742
01:05:32,180 --> 01:05:36,040
 And so many people asked me, what is, what was your husband going?

743
01:05:36,040 --> 01:05:38,740
 Like, what was going on with your husband during this whole time?

744
01:05:38,740 --> 01:05:40,140
 And I just wanted to.

745
01:05:40,140 --> 01:05:40,820
 Yeah, exactly.

746
01:05:40,820 --> 01:05:42,200
 I took the question from your mouth.

747
01:05:42,200 --> 01:05:45,520
 Because you can imagine, people ask me that all the time.

748
01:05:45,520 --> 01:05:54,100
 And my poor husband, I love him so dearly because he loves me so much.

749
01:05:54,100 --> 01:06:00,540
 I'm very, I've always, I was always very proud and I lacked a lot of humility.

750
01:06:00,540 --> 01:06:04,960
 And I was always very strong-willed.

751
01:06:04,960 --> 01:06:08,700
 And I think part of that is because I always had to depend on myself.

752
01:06:08,700 --> 01:06:12,660
 I didn't know how to depend on anyone else.

753
01:06:13,200 --> 01:06:15,740
 And the men in my life had always failed me.

754
01:06:15,740 --> 01:06:20,380
 And I was with this wonderful man who loved me.

755
01:06:20,380 --> 01:06:23,860
 And I didn't know how to trust him in that way.

756
01:06:23,860 --> 01:06:26,880
 To just depend on him and rely on him.

757
01:06:26,880 --> 01:06:30,100
 I always thought I had to do everything, you know?

758
01:06:30,100 --> 01:06:33,980
 And so he was telling me, I don't understand.

759
01:06:33,980 --> 01:06:35,020
 Just quit your job.

760
01:06:35,020 --> 01:06:36,340
 The whole time.

761
01:06:37,080 --> 01:06:39,400
 The whole time, he said, I don't understand.

762
01:06:39,400 --> 01:06:40,560
 Just quit your job.

763
01:06:40,560 --> 01:06:43,620
 And I thought, what do you mean you don't understand, you know?

764
01:06:43,620 --> 01:06:46,040
 What are we going to do about this?

765
01:06:46,040 --> 01:06:47,900
 How are we going to pay the house?

766
01:06:47,900 --> 01:06:49,140
 And how are we going to pay this?

767
01:06:49,140 --> 01:06:53,060
 And, you know, I'm like, do you not understand that there's, we have a budget.

768
01:06:53,060 --> 01:06:54,460
 We have bills to pay.

769
01:06:54,460 --> 01:06:55,040
 We have a budget.

770
01:06:55,040 --> 01:06:57,100
 And what are we going to do without my income?

771
01:06:57,100 --> 01:06:58,540
 And he said, just quit.

772
01:06:58,540 --> 01:06:59,500
 We'll be okay.

773
01:07:00,140 --> 01:07:01,860
 And I thought, no, I can't.

774
01:07:01,860 --> 01:07:03,460
 It doesn't work that way, you know?

775
01:07:03,460 --> 01:07:08,440
 And so here I was going through this.

776
01:07:08,440 --> 01:07:10,860
 I felt like I was going through it alone, you know?

777
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:16,660
 And so there, you know, I had that moment where he was comforting me.

778
01:07:16,660 --> 01:07:19,440
 And he just said, you're going to be, it's going to be okay, you know?

779
01:07:19,440 --> 01:07:21,940
 And nothing else was spoken.

780
01:07:21,940 --> 01:07:22,940
 Just tears.

781
01:07:23,280 --> 01:07:34,080
 And then when I went back to work the following day, I just, I felt this heaviness, you know, of now this sense of urgency.

782
01:07:34,080 --> 01:07:35,060
 I have to quit.

783
01:07:35,060 --> 01:07:36,660
 I don't know when that's going to be.

784
01:07:36,660 --> 01:07:39,580
 I have to find another job quickly.

785
01:07:39,580 --> 01:07:45,680
 I wasn't finding anything, which is incredible because normally I would, was able to find a job very easily.

786
01:07:45,680 --> 01:07:47,160
 But it wasn't happening.

787
01:07:48,160 --> 01:07:53,400
 So I went back to Mass the following Sunday, which was the first Sunday after Easter.

788
01:07:53,400 --> 01:07:55,880
 We know that is Divine Mercy Sunday.

789
01:07:55,880 --> 01:07:57,080
 I didn't know that.

790
01:07:57,080 --> 01:08:02,900
 I didn't have a clue because at this point in my life, I was like a brand new Catholic.

791
01:08:02,900 --> 01:08:08,160
 And I was not familiar with any of the feast days or even what that meant.

792
01:08:08,160 --> 01:08:10,940
 It was May the 1st, 2011.

793
01:08:10,940 --> 01:08:12,320
 I'll never forget the date.

794
01:08:12,320 --> 01:08:17,820
 Today is the anniversary of that Divine Mercy Sunday.

795
01:08:17,820 --> 01:08:19,960
 Yes, May the 1st, 2011.

796
01:08:19,960 --> 01:08:23,200
 I didn't know what that meant.

797
01:08:23,200 --> 01:08:35,400
 But also, it was also the date of the beatification of St. John Paul II, who we know to be, was the most staunch defender and outspoken defender of life.

798
01:08:35,400 --> 01:08:39,580
 And so no coincidence there at all.

799
01:08:39,580 --> 01:08:56,240
 I was sitting in Mass with my family and throughout the entire Mass, I was just praying to God to help me, to give me some insight, something, some sign, anything to help me do what I needed to do.

800
01:08:56,480 --> 01:08:59,660
 And give me the strength and give me the strength and the grace to take a leap of faith.

801
01:08:59,660 --> 01:09:07,000
 And he spoke to me throughout the entire Mass, through the scriptures, through the songs, through the hymns, everything.

802
01:09:07,000 --> 01:09:18,480
 And it was during the moment of consecration of the Eucharist that it was such a powerful moment.

803
01:09:18,480 --> 01:09:24,480
 Because, you know, as Catholics, we are always taught about the true presence of Jesus in the Eucharist.

804
01:09:24,480 --> 01:09:36,300
 And this is why this moment led me to understand not just the reality of that, but also to really finally understand Jesus on the cross.

805
01:09:36,300 --> 01:09:43,440
 And so it was during the consecration of the Eucharist that I heard God say very clearly to me.

806
01:09:43,440 --> 01:09:51,660
 It was when the priest was lifting up the host that I heard God say, Ramona, have faith in me.

807
01:09:51,660 --> 01:09:52,420
 I forgive you.

808
01:09:53,140 --> 01:09:54,600
 And I began to cry.

809
01:09:54,600 --> 01:10:02,660
 And it was such a very audible, you know, like, I can't even explain it.

810
01:10:02,660 --> 01:10:04,160
 You know, just so clear.

811
01:10:04,160 --> 01:10:05,540
 Ramona, I forgive you.

812
01:10:05,540 --> 01:10:06,340
 Have faith in me.

813
01:10:06,340 --> 01:10:09,580
 And I cried.

814
01:10:09,580 --> 01:10:14,460
 And I just knew at that moment what God was saying, you know, to trust.

815
01:10:14,460 --> 01:10:23,040
 And that's with me not knowing anything about divine mercy, not even knowing that the words, Jesus, I trust in you, are written on the image.

816
01:10:23,140 --> 01:10:24,340
 I knew nothing of that.

817
01:10:24,340 --> 01:10:26,760
 I didn't even know that what that image meant.

818
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:28,080
 You know, I'd seen it.

819
01:10:28,080 --> 01:10:28,840
 I never knew.

820
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:35,260
 And so he was calling me to trust him and to take a leap of faith.

821
01:10:35,660 --> 01:10:41,740
 And so when we walked out of mass that day, I knew, I knew I couldn't, I couldn't go on.

822
01:10:42,220 --> 01:10:43,880
 And I had Monday off.

823
01:10:43,880 --> 01:10:53,680
 So we were only open three days a week, which is really incredible because the number three is very significant throughout my story and just in my whole life in general.

824
01:10:54,360 --> 01:10:59,180
 We worked, I worked at Planned Parenthood three days a week and we, I was there three years.

825
01:10:59,180 --> 01:11:05,540
 On the third day of the 40 Days for Life campaign, I went and asked for prayers and we had three children at the time.

826
01:11:05,540 --> 01:11:07,060
 I was 33 years old.

827
01:11:07,060 --> 01:11:10,640
 Very significant.

828
01:11:11,920 --> 01:11:18,400
 But I, I, I went back to work, what we were closed on Mondays and we're open Tuesday, Wednesday, Friday.

829
01:11:18,400 --> 01:11:27,060
 And so on Monday, I was just very, I had so much peace because I knew I was going to quit.

830
01:11:27,060 --> 01:11:32,680
 I didn't know exactly when I had in my mind at the end of the month, but I had so much peace.

831
01:11:32,680 --> 01:11:35,600
 And then on Tuesday, I had to go back to work.

832
01:11:35,600 --> 01:11:41,200
 And I remember just getting up that day, just feeling so much dread, like, oh, I don't want to go, you know?

833
01:11:41,200 --> 01:11:44,880
 And I thought, okay, I'm going to quit this week.

834
01:11:44,880 --> 01:11:46,540
 I'm, this is going to be it.

835
01:11:46,540 --> 01:11:48,960
 I'm not going to, I'm not going to go after this.

836
01:11:48,960 --> 01:12:02,500
 And so on my drive to work, I was praying to God to protect me in those final three days from all occasions of sin, from any referrals for abortion.

837
01:12:02,680 --> 01:12:17,960
 And so when I got to work, I received a phone call from the admin administration telling me that I needed to reschedule all of our patients because our nurse practitioner had to cover another clinic.

838
01:12:17,960 --> 01:12:22,760
 And because she had to cover another clinic, that meant no one would be there.

839
01:12:22,760 --> 01:12:26,200
 I was going to be there alone and I was going to reschedule everyone.

840
01:12:26,200 --> 01:12:29,460
 And so I was calling all the women to reschedule them.

841
01:12:29,460 --> 01:12:32,920
 And I didn't have to see anybody.

842
01:12:32,920 --> 01:12:35,160
 I didn't sell any contraception.

843
01:12:35,160 --> 01:12:46,420
 And on the third day of the week, so on Friday, on May the 6th of 2011, so I'll celebrate 14 years this May 6th since I left Planned Parenthood.

844
01:12:46,420 --> 01:12:57,420
 But on that Friday, I was probably about an hour away from walking out of Planned Parenthood when a woman came in for a pregnancy test.

845
01:12:57,420 --> 01:13:06,680
 And on the intake form, it asks the question, you know, if your pregnancy test is positive, you know, what type of referral would you like?

846
01:13:06,680 --> 01:13:11,360
 And she had checked the box abortion, adoption, and prenatal care.

847
01:13:11,840 --> 01:13:13,820
 So she marked, checked all three boxes.

848
01:13:13,820 --> 01:13:21,020
 And usually in the past, when women would check all three boxes, it usually meant that they wanted an abortion.

849
01:13:21,020 --> 01:13:22,260
 They just didn't want to say it.

850
01:13:22,260 --> 01:13:29,480
 And I remember walking her to the back of, you know, the clinic to sit her down in the exam room.

851
01:13:29,480 --> 01:13:33,900
 And I looked up to God and I thought, oh, why are you doing this to me?

852
01:13:33,900 --> 01:13:35,280
 I'm about to leave.

853
01:13:35,280 --> 01:13:35,640
 Why?

854
01:13:35,640 --> 01:13:37,000
 You know, why are you doing this?

855
01:13:37,000 --> 01:13:39,640
 And her pregnancy test was positive.

856
01:13:40,440 --> 01:13:43,660
 And I went in the room and I congratulated her on her pregnancy.

857
01:13:43,660 --> 01:13:45,560
 And she began to cry.

858
01:13:45,560 --> 01:13:51,100
 And when she cried, I just looked at her and I said, what's, you know, what's wrong?

859
01:13:51,100 --> 01:13:53,820
 And she said, I don't know if I can have this baby.

860
01:13:53,820 --> 01:13:55,820
 I think she was in her early 20s.

861
01:13:55,820 --> 01:13:59,900
 And she had already had a daughter, a little girl.

862
01:13:59,900 --> 01:14:01,440
 I think she was maybe three years old.

863
01:14:01,440 --> 01:14:04,040
 And she said, I don't know if I can have this baby.

864
01:14:04,040 --> 01:14:07,840
 And I said, just, you know, tell me a little bit more about that.

865
01:14:07,840 --> 01:14:11,360
 And she said, well, the father of this baby is in jail.

866
01:14:11,360 --> 01:14:12,120
 He's abusive.

867
01:14:12,120 --> 01:14:17,940
 And I don't know what I'm going to do if he gets out, you know, and I have this baby.

868
01:14:17,940 --> 01:14:21,540
 And I don't know.

869
01:14:21,540 --> 01:14:24,200
 I just connected with her on that.

870
01:14:25,000 --> 01:14:26,720
 And I told her my story.

871
01:14:26,720 --> 01:14:33,860
 And I shared with her the abuse that I had dealt with and that I was a survivor of domestic abuse.

872
01:14:33,860 --> 01:14:38,300
 And I told her how I found the strength, that God gave me the strength to leave.

873
01:14:38,300 --> 01:14:40,500
 And I just shared my own personal journey.

874
01:14:41,360 --> 01:14:45,600
 And I asked her about her faith in God because she had a little cross on her neck.

875
01:14:45,600 --> 01:14:48,840
 And she told me that, yes, she believed in God.

876
01:14:48,840 --> 01:14:58,060
 And she didn't know that, you know, she was more concerned about what would happen with the father than, you know, she had her family support.

877
01:14:58,060 --> 01:14:59,880
 She had everything in place.

878
01:15:00,100 --> 01:15:11,160
 And so we just, we spoke and I just shared my own testimony with her about my past relationship and how I'd found a good man in my life.

879
01:15:11,480 --> 01:15:16,980
 And she stood up and she threw her arms around my neck and she was crying and she said, thank you so much.

880
01:15:16,980 --> 01:15:17,860
 I'm going to keep my baby.

881
01:15:17,860 --> 01:15:25,240
 So she left and I cried and I thought, wow, I can't believe that just happened.

882
01:15:25,240 --> 01:15:28,440
 And I walked out.

883
01:15:28,440 --> 01:15:32,600
 I submitted my letter of resignation and I walked out of Planned Parenthood.

884
01:15:32,600 --> 01:15:37,960
 And I realized in that moment that that was my moment of redemption.

885
01:15:39,000 --> 01:15:51,040
 Because all of the times that I had referred women for abortion, you know, I just never stopped and affirmed them in life, life affirming choices.

886
01:15:51,040 --> 01:15:53,540
 I never helped them make those life affirming choices.

887
01:15:53,540 --> 01:15:56,720
 Rather, I was just quick to give them the referral for abortion.

888
01:15:56,720 --> 01:15:57,960
 Oh, you want an abortion here?

889
01:15:57,960 --> 01:16:07,780
 You know, but it was just a beautiful moment and so profound that God would do that for me in those final hours at Planned Parenthood.

890
01:16:08,100 --> 01:16:11,420
 And so I walked out, I quit, left my keys on the desk.

891
01:16:11,420 --> 01:16:12,960
 No one knew it was going to happen.

892
01:16:12,960 --> 01:16:15,320
 You know, I gave no warning, you know.

893
01:16:15,320 --> 01:16:22,940
 And then three months later, I got a call that the facility was going to shut down.

894
01:16:22,940 --> 01:16:31,020
 And I was invited to come speak at the closing celebration rally of the Planned Parenthood that I had once directed.

895
01:16:32,520 --> 01:16:34,900
 So, what did you do then?

896
01:16:34,900 --> 01:16:37,540
 At the rally?

897
01:16:37,540 --> 01:16:38,300
 Yes.

898
01:16:38,300 --> 01:16:39,640
 So at the rally, we were...

899
01:16:39,640 --> 01:16:40,280
 Who called you?

900
01:16:40,280 --> 01:16:41,200
 David B. Wright.

901
01:16:41,200 --> 01:16:42,360
 David B. Wright.

902
01:16:42,360 --> 01:16:42,620
 Yeah.

903
01:16:42,620 --> 01:16:43,840
 So he...

904
01:16:43,840 --> 01:16:45,200
 He started the 40 Days for Life.

905
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:45,880
 He started, yep.

906
01:16:45,880 --> 01:16:47,300
 Started 40 Days for Life.

907
01:16:47,300 --> 01:16:48,700
 And, well, it could have been David.

908
01:16:48,700 --> 01:16:49,140
 I don't know.

909
01:16:49,140 --> 01:16:52,000
 It was someone on the team who invited me out.

910
01:16:52,120 --> 01:16:56,600
 And David was there to lead the celebration.

911
01:16:56,960 --> 01:17:03,680
 And so all the people were gathered there who had been out there praying, you know, the director of the Pregnancy Resource Center.

912
01:17:03,680 --> 01:17:07,440
 Like, all of the pro-life leaders and groups were out there to celebrate the closing.

913
01:17:07,440 --> 01:17:10,840
 And they asked me to come out and just share a few words.

914
01:17:10,840 --> 01:17:12,180
 And I did.

915
01:17:12,520 --> 01:17:21,580
 And I think that was kind of that moment where people were going, you know, they saw the video and they were like, whoa, wait a minute, you know.

916
01:17:21,580 --> 01:17:25,700
 And that kind of led me to all of this, I guess you could say.

917
01:17:26,260 --> 01:17:30,640
 But what was amazing is that I was pregnant during the rally.

918
01:17:30,640 --> 01:17:33,840
 So I was, at that point, two months pregnant.

919
01:17:33,840 --> 01:17:43,040
 A month after I quit Planned Parenthood, my husband and I had our first, the first of the four conversion babies that we have today.

920
01:17:43,040 --> 01:17:53,940
 And despite physicians telling me, you know, that I would have difficulties getting pregnant, we had our first conversion baby.

921
01:17:54,240 --> 01:17:59,840
 And then three years later, we had our second, but, well, we lost one.

922
01:17:59,840 --> 01:18:02,680
 And three years later, we'd lost our baby.

923
01:18:02,680 --> 01:18:07,100
 And then the doctor said that I probably wouldn't be able to conceive.

924
01:18:07,100 --> 01:18:09,600
 I would probably miscarry again.

925
01:18:09,600 --> 01:18:11,560
 But we conceived a month later.

926
01:18:11,560 --> 01:18:15,380
 And we had our third, at that point, third baby.

927
01:18:15,380 --> 01:18:18,400
 And then three years later, we had our next baby.

928
01:18:19,540 --> 01:18:29,400
 And so, yeah, we had all of these new lives that I look at and I think, you wouldn't be here had I never had a conversion.

929
01:18:29,400 --> 01:18:31,720
 Because we were not open to life.

930
01:18:31,720 --> 01:18:37,980
 We were not open to having more children or open to the blessings that God wanted to give us.

931
01:18:38,400 --> 01:18:40,760
 And as you can imagine, it was a struggle.

932
01:18:40,760 --> 01:18:43,700
 It was a struggle when I would get pregnant.

933
01:18:43,700 --> 01:18:53,960
 Well, first of all, medically speaking, I, it was a struggle because I had to have injections, progesterone injections, to help keep me from going into early labor.

934
01:18:53,960 --> 01:18:58,040
 Because with all of them, I was already having contractions in my first trimester.

935
01:18:58,560 --> 01:19:03,040
 So it was, you know, always the fear that I was going to lose the babies.

936
01:19:03,040 --> 01:19:06,780
 And they didn't come premature.

937
01:19:06,780 --> 01:19:08,720
 They all came early, but they weren't premature.

938
01:19:08,720 --> 01:19:12,020
 And so, thanks be to God, they were all born healthy.

939
01:19:12,020 --> 01:19:17,320
 But it was, it was a struggle for me to have my babies.

940
01:19:17,320 --> 01:19:27,120
 Emotionally, it was hard because there were friends of mine who struggled with infertility, who were unable to have babies.

941
01:19:27,900 --> 01:19:34,000
 And a dear friend of mine as well, who had miscarried many children and unable to have her own.

942
01:19:34,000 --> 01:19:38,740
 And so I think those were probably some of the most difficult times for me spiritually.

943
01:19:38,740 --> 01:19:51,940
 Because I felt spiritually attacked for, and guilt, guilted into feeling bad for, for being pregnant when other women, you know, that had lived such beautiful faith-filled lives,

944
01:19:51,940 --> 01:19:56,740
 who had always been pro-life, who had always been close to God, were unable to have children.

945
01:19:57,240 --> 01:20:02,980
 And I think that was really part of the spiritual attack that I experienced, especially when I was pregnant.

946
01:20:03,980 --> 01:20:07,160
 Feeling like I didn't deserve, you know, feeling like I didn't deserve, you know, to have babies.

947
01:20:07,160 --> 01:20:10,840
 And, of course, you know, trust Jesus, I trust in you.

948
01:20:10,840 --> 01:20:13,900
 You know, I had to keep coming back to Jesus, I trust in you.

949
01:20:14,140 --> 01:20:25,060
 And really trying to be close to God during those times, because I knew that I should never reject the blessings that God was giving me.

950
01:20:25,060 --> 01:20:28,540
 But, of course, the enemy wants to rob us of that.

951
01:20:28,540 --> 01:20:30,360
 So it was a tough time.

952
01:20:30,880 --> 01:20:38,540
 So, Ramona, you and your husband, now you have seven children together, and one of them is on heaven, right?

953
01:20:38,540 --> 01:20:38,920
 Yeah.

954
01:20:38,920 --> 01:20:43,400
 Can you tell me more about the names of the children?

955
01:20:43,400 --> 01:20:49,620
 How did you choose them and those four, especially?

956
01:20:49,620 --> 01:20:50,360
 Yeah.

957
01:20:50,360 --> 01:20:53,660
 So my first daughter is Lorena.

958
01:20:53,660 --> 01:20:57,540
 And it was nothing significant at the time.

959
01:20:57,540 --> 01:20:58,620
 You know, I was a young girl.

960
01:20:58,620 --> 01:21:01,400
 And then my stepdaughter is Savannah.

961
01:21:01,400 --> 01:21:04,580
 So my husband and, you know, they chose that.

962
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:09,320
 But then the son that we had together, our first child we had together, is Elijah.

963
01:21:09,320 --> 01:21:12,460
 And I always loved the name Elijah.

964
01:21:12,460 --> 01:21:15,180
 Just, it's beautiful, biblical.

965
01:21:15,180 --> 01:21:18,320
 It's just a very strong name.

966
01:21:18,320 --> 01:21:25,440
 And I knew that if we ever had a son, you know, he would be Elijah.

967
01:21:25,440 --> 01:21:27,560
 And it's just very fitting with him being premature.

968
01:21:27,560 --> 01:21:31,920
 And then he just grew up to be such a tall, strong young man.

969
01:21:32,660 --> 01:21:39,700
 And then when I left Planned Parenthood and we had our next children, we named our son Philip.

970
01:21:39,700 --> 01:21:43,160
 And same thing, just a biblical name.

971
01:21:43,160 --> 01:21:46,020
 I always liked the name Philip as well.

972
01:21:46,020 --> 01:21:48,700
 But also my brother-in-law is named Philip.

973
01:21:48,700 --> 01:21:53,220
 And so it's kind of funny because my husband is one of six kids.

974
01:21:53,220 --> 01:21:59,640
 And all of the nieces and nephews, someone is named after one of the siblings of my husband.

975
01:21:59,640 --> 01:22:02,460
 Whether it be a middle name or a first name.

976
01:22:02,600 --> 01:22:07,440
 And so Philip, my brother-in-law Philip, is the only one that didn't have someone named after him.

977
01:22:07,440 --> 01:22:09,200
 So we chose Philip.

978
01:22:09,200 --> 01:22:15,740
 But also my brother-in-law's birthday is May the 6th, which is the date that I left Planned Parenthood.

979
01:22:15,740 --> 01:22:20,760
 And so when we became pregnant with our son Philip, I thought it was fitting to name him Philip.

980
01:22:20,760 --> 01:22:24,820
 And then Philip David and David being after my dad.

981
01:22:25,760 --> 01:22:29,480
 And then we had Ramaya, which is Ramaya Elizabeth.

982
01:22:29,480 --> 01:22:31,960
 She's also, that's also a biblical name.

983
01:22:31,960 --> 01:22:33,960
 It's found one time in the Bible.

984
01:22:34,600 --> 01:22:38,720
 So just wanted someone with the letter R after me.

985
01:22:39,440 --> 01:22:45,840
 And then, well, before Ramaya, we lost our baby very early miscarriage.

986
01:22:45,840 --> 01:22:47,960
 But we named the baby Guadalupe.

987
01:22:47,960 --> 01:22:52,980
 Just because I said I think I was pregnant with a girl.

988
01:22:52,980 --> 01:22:54,480
 My husband thinks it was a boy.

989
01:22:54,480 --> 01:22:56,840
 And so Guadalupe fit both.

990
01:22:57,280 --> 01:23:03,660
 And my grandmother and grandfather, my maternal grandmother and grandfather were both named Guadalupe.

991
01:23:03,660 --> 01:23:08,860
 So I thought that was beautiful to honor my grandparents and then also Our Lady.

992
01:23:08,860 --> 01:23:13,360
 And then Ramaya, we had Ramaya and then we have now Zoe.

993
01:23:13,360 --> 01:23:16,600
 And Zoe is life.

994
01:23:16,600 --> 01:23:21,620
 It means, yes, literally a Greek for Eve, which is life.

995
01:23:22,080 --> 01:23:27,540
 And I knew that would be the perfect name for her because I was much older.

996
01:23:27,540 --> 01:23:33,240
 When I had her, I was under a lot of spiritual attack when I became pregnant with her.

997
01:23:33,240 --> 01:23:36,920
 And life overcame all of that.

998
01:23:36,920 --> 01:23:40,020
 So, yeah, I thought Zoe was very fitting.

999
01:23:40,020 --> 01:23:41,300
 This is so beautiful.

1000
01:23:41,300 --> 01:23:42,640
 We talked yesterday.

1001
01:23:42,640 --> 01:23:50,500
 We have some of the similar things in our life about some dates and everything.

1002
01:23:50,500 --> 01:23:55,060
 And now, as you're saying about those names, my sister has four children.

1003
01:23:55,060 --> 01:24:01,480
 And their names are Eve, Philip, Laura, and Elijah.

1004
01:24:01,480 --> 01:24:04,960
 Oh, that's fantastic.

1005
01:24:04,960 --> 01:24:05,840
 That's so good.

1006
01:24:05,840 --> 01:24:06,580
 I love it.

1007
01:24:06,580 --> 01:24:07,220
 I love it.

1008
01:24:07,220 --> 01:24:08,880
 I call those God kisses.

1009
01:24:08,880 --> 01:24:15,540
 I like to, I think it's just a way that God just reminds us that he's always with us.

1010
01:24:16,080 --> 01:24:19,040
 Especially in my traveling, I always meet people.

1011
01:24:19,040 --> 01:24:26,140
 And we always find that there's things that are, that we can, we find similarities or ways in which we're connected to one another.

1012
01:24:26,140 --> 01:24:30,700
 And I always just think that God is up there just smiling and giving a little kiss to us.

1013
01:24:30,700 --> 01:24:31,360
 Yes.

1014
01:24:31,920 --> 01:24:34,180
 Thank you, Ramona, for this talk.

1015
01:24:34,180 --> 01:24:40,620
 Thank you so much for this great God kiss that you gave us here.

1016
01:24:40,620 --> 01:24:46,900
 And I wish you blessed staying here in Croatia, Europe, and that you come again.

1017
01:24:46,900 --> 01:24:47,980
 Absolutely.

1018
01:24:47,980 --> 01:24:52,240
 I'm very grateful to be here and it's always such a privilege.

1019
01:24:52,240 --> 01:24:52,800
 Thank you.

1020
01:24:52,800 --> 01:24:53,960
 Thank you so much.

1021
01:24:54,960 --> 01:25:01,020
 Dragi pratitelji YouTube kanala Udruge Hrvatska za život, bio je ovo još jedan podcast život.

1022
01:25:01,020 --> 01:25:05,720
 Ugostili smo Ramonu Trevino iz Teksasa u Americi.

1023
01:25:05,720 --> 01:25:12,620
 Pratite nas i dalje i imate još ispod našeg videa objavljene druge videe.

1024
01:25:12,620 --> 01:25:14,040
 Hvala nisu si Marija.

1025
01:25:16,100 --> 01:25:26,420
 Hvala nisu si Marija.

